main event: A hovering, silent object was observed for 15 minutes in Wapello, Iowa on 3/7/67.
interesting points: The object emitted no lights and made no sound.
The witnesses could not estimate the size or altitude of the object.
No aircraft were reported in the area at the time of the sighting.
On 3/29/67, two bright lights moving slowly were observed in Wapello, Iowa, then suddenly shot up vertically at a high rate of speed.
On 5/22/67, a farmer observed a 4 ft diameter circular saucer-type object move from north to south at a fast speed about 1,000 ft above ground level.
sighted object: A hovering, silent object; two bright lights that shot up vertically; a circular saucer-type object
witnesses: Mr. and Mrs. Carl A. Schlieckert; two unnamed witnesses; M.T. Smith - farmer
